  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT380-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">paṉipparuvaṅ kuṟittup pirintāṉ talaimakaṉ piriya “paruvavaraviṉkaṇ
          vēṟupaṭuvāḷ āyiṉuṅ katumeṉa āṟṟuvippatu aritu” eṉṉuṅ karuttiṉā¬ḷāyk kūtirp paruvattut
          talaimakaḷ/ṉ kēṭpat taṉatu āṟṟāmai viḷaṅkat tōḻi colliyatu. </p>


        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">He separated intending to [use] the season of dew; as HE
          separated, spoken by the confidante to make clear her lack of strength, for HER to hear in
          the cold season, as one, who thought “difficult is it to comfort [her] efficiently(?),
          although she changes at the coming of the season”. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT380">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> vicumpukaṇ putaiyap pāay vēntar</l>
          <l> veṉṟeṟi muraci ṉaṉpala muḻaṅkip</l>
          <l> peyalā ṉātē vāṉaṅ kātalar</l>
          <l> naṉicēy nāṭṭar nammuṉ ṉalarē</l>
          <l> yāṅkucacey vāṅko ṟōḻi yīṅkaiya</l>
          <l> vaṇṇat tuymmala rutira</l>
          <l> muṉṉart tōṉṟum paṉikkaṭu nāḷē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l> Spread, so that the sky's eye is buried, [and] thundering</l>
          <l rend="indent2"> good many [beats] like the drum beaten by a victorious king,</l>
          <l>raining [is] unending.</l>
          <l rend="indent6"> The heavenly lover,</l>
          <l> being in a very distant land, doesn't approach us.</l>
          <l> What will we do, friend,</l>
          <l rend="indent"> in the harsh days of frost, appearing before [us],</l>
          <l rend="indent2"> so that blossoms drop off in colourful filaments?</l>

          <lg type="alternate" sameAs="3b" resp="#TVG">
            <l>the sky is unending in raining.</l>
          </lg>

        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
